HEADWORD: Matter-of-fact
<hw>Mat"ter-of-fact"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Adhering to
facts; not turning aside from absolute realities; not fanciful or
imaginative; commonplace; dry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mattery</ent>⟦br⟧
